{
  "video_id": "tBzSLu3MZ6I",
  "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tBzSLu3MZ6I",
  "transcript": [
    {
      "text": "- Take a look at recent history",
      "start": 1.491,
      "duration": 2.512
    },
    {
      "text": "since the second World War.",
      "start": 4.003,
      "duration": 2.517
    },
    {
      "text": "Something really remarkable has happened.",
      "start": 6.52,
      "duration": 3.814
    },
    {
      "text": "First, human intelligence created",
      "start": 10.334,
      "duration": 2.75
    },
    {
      "text": "two huge sledge hammers capable",
      "start": 16.962,
      "duration": 2.583
    },
    {
      "text": "of terminating our existence",
      "start": 22.657,
      "duration": 1.906
    },
    {
      "text": "or at least organized existence.",
      "start": 24.563,
      "duration": 2.538
    },
    {
      "text": "Both from the second World War.",
      "start": 27.101,
      "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
      "text": "One of them's familiar.",
      "start": 30.301,
      "duration": 1.702
    },
    {
      "text": "- A scientific thunderbolt gives",
      "start": 32.003,
      "duration": 1.818
    },
    {
      "text": "a preview of its destructive force.",
      "start": 33.821,
      "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
      "text": "One of Japan's arsenal cities was selected",
      "start": 37.181,
      "duration": 2.139
    },
    {
      "text": "as the first to feel the weight",
      "start": 39.32,
      "duration": 1.799
    },
    {
      "text": "of atomic power.",
      "start": 41.119,
      "duration": 1.342
    },
    {
      "text": "- It was immediately obvious",
      "start": 42.461,
      "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
      "text": "on August 6, 1945,",
      "start": 44.221,
      "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
      "text": "a day that I remember very well.",
      "start": 48.117,
      "duration": 3.123
    },
    {
      "text": "It was obvious that soon technology would",
      "start": 51.24,
      "duration": 3.483
    },
    {
      "text": "develop to the point where it would",
      "start": 54.723,
      "duration": 2.197
    },
    {
      "text": "lead to terminal disaster.",
      "start": 56.92,
      "duration": 2.796
    },
    {
      "text": "The scientists certainly understood this.",
      "start": 59.716,
      "duration": 2.127
    },
    {
      "text": "In 1947,",
      "start": 61.843,
      "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
      "text": "the Bulletin of Atomic Scientists",
      "start": 63.816,
      "duration": 2.384
    },
    {
      "text": "inaugurated its famous doomsday clock.",
      "start": 66.2,
      "duration": 3.701
    },
    {
      "text": "How close is the minute hand to midnight?",
      "start": 69.901,
      "duration": 3.339
    },
    {
      "text": "And environmental disaster which wasn't",
      "start": 73.24,
      "duration": 3.179
    },
    {
      "text": "thought about much in 1945,",
      "start": 76.419,
      "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
      "text": "but it turns out we now understand",
      "start": 79.761,
      "duration": 3.42
    },
    {
      "text": "that at the end of the second World War",
      "start": 83.181,
      "duration": 2.619
    },
    {
      "text": "the world also entered into a new",
      "start": 85.8,
      "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
      "text": "geological epoch.",
      "start": 88.84,
      "duration": 1.861
    },
    {
      "text": "It's called the anthropocene,",
      "start": 90.701,
      "duration": 1.621
    },
    {
      "text": "the epoch in which humans have",
      "start": 92.322,
      "duration": 2.813
    },
    {
      "text": "a severe, in fact, maybe disastrous impact",
      "start": 95.135,
      "duration": 4.004
    },
    {
      "text": "on the environment.",
      "start": 99.139,
      "duration": 1.601
    },
    {
      "text": "There was a sharp spike in such activities",
      "start": 100.74,
      "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
      "text": "and disaster after 1945.",
      "start": 104.02,
      "duration": 2.783
    },
    {
      "text": "So, geologists pretty much even formally",
      "start": 106.803,
      "duration": 2.858
    },
    {
      "text": "date the origin of the\nanthropocene to about",
      "start": 109.661,
      "duration": 3.9
    },
    {
      "text": "the same time as the nuclear age.",
      "start": 113.561,
      "duration": 2.75
    },
    {
      "text": "Observing that the\nBulletin analysts in 2015",
      "start": 117.699,
      "duration": 3.667
    },
    {
      "text": "mentioned both",
      "start": 123.283,
      "duration": 1.543
    },
    {
      "text": "and moved the clock to\nthree minutes to midnight,",
      "start": 124.826,
      "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
      "text": "the closest it had been since 1984.",
      "start": 127.546,
      "duration": 3.637
    },
    {
      "text": "Immediately after the Trump election,",
      "start": 131.183,
      "duration": 2.502
    },
    {
      "text": "late January this year,",
      "start": 133.685,
      "duration": 2.054
    },
    {
      "text": "the clock was moved again to two",
      "start": 135.739,
      "duration": 2.157
    },
    {
      "text": "and a half minutes to midnight.",
      "start": 137.896,
      "duration": 2.567
    },
    {
      "text": "Closest it's been since '53.",
      "start": 140.463,
      "duration": 2.741
    },
    {
      "text": "So, there's the two existential threats",
      "start": 143.204,
      "duration": 3.211
    },
    {
      "text": "that we've created.",
      "start": 146.415,
      "duration": 2.149
    },
    {
      "text": "In the case of nuclear war,",
      "start": 148.564,
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "text": "maybe wipe us out.",
      "start": 150.564,
      "duration": 1.414
    },
    {
      "text": "In case of environmental catastrophe,",
      "start": 151.978,
      "duration": 1.663
    },
    {
      "text": "severe impact.",
      "start": 153.641,
      "duration": 1.167
    },
    {
      "text": "Then a third thing happened.",
      "start": 155.721,
      "duration": 2.182
    },
    {
      "text": "Beginning around the '70s,",
      "start": 157.903,
      "duration": 1.882
    },
    {
      "text": "human intelligence dedicated itself",
      "start": 159.785,
      "duration": 2.016
    },
    {
      "text": "to eliminating,",
      "start": 161.801,
      "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
      "text": "or at least weakening,",
      "start": 163.945,
      "duration": 1.895
    },
    {
      "text": "the main barrier against",
      "start": 165.84,
      "duration": 2.025
    },
    {
      "text": "the threats.",
      "start": 167.865,
      "duration": 1.608
    },
    {
      "text": "It's called neoliberalism.",
      "start": 169.473,
      "duration": 2.197
    },
    {
      "text": "If you ask yourself,",
      "start": 171.67,
      "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
      "text": "it was a transition at that period",
      "start": 173.19,
      "duration": 2.603
    },
    {
      "text": "from the period of what some people call",
      "start": 175.793,
      "duration": 3.501
    },
    {
      "text": "regimented capitalism, '50s and '60s,",
      "start": 179.294,
      "duration": 2.803
    },
    {
      "text": "the great growth period,",
      "start": 182.097,
      "duration": 1.556
    },
    {
      "text": "egalitarian growth.",
      "start": 183.653,
      "duration": 1.82
    },
    {
      "text": "A lot of advances",
      "start": 185.473,
      "duration": 1.002
    },
    {
      "text": "and social justice and so on.",
      "start": 186.475,
      "duration": 3.118
    },
    {
      "text": "That changed in the '70s",
      "start": 189.593,
      "duration": 1.704
    },
    {
      "text": "with the onset of the neoliberal era",
      "start": 191.297,
      "duration": 3.776
    },
    {
      "text": "that we've been living in since.",
      "start": 195.073,
      "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
      "text": "- We deregulated the airlines,",
      "start": 197.553,
      "duration": 2.026
    },
    {
      "text": "we deregulated the trucking industry,",
      "start": 199.579,
      "duration": 1.899
    },
    {
      "text": "we deregulated financial institutions,",
      "start": 201.478,
      "duration": 2.657
    },
    {
      "text": "we decontrolled oil\nand natural gas prices,",
      "start": 204.135,
      "duration": 3.261
    },
    {
      "text": "and we negotiated lower trade barriers",
      "start": 207.396,
      "duration": 1.621
    },
    {
      "text": "throughout the world",
      "start": 209.017,
      "duration": 1.581
    },
    {
      "text": "to get rid of needless",
      "start": 210.598,
      "duration": 1.883
    },
    {
      "text": "and burdensome federal regulations",
      "start": 212.481,
      "duration": 2.458
    },
    {
      "text": "which benefit nobody",
      "start": 214.939,
      "duration": 1.419
    },
    {
      "text": "and which harm all of us.",
      "start": 216.358,
      "duration": 2.083
    },
    {
      "text": "- And if you ask yourself\nwhat this era is,",
      "start": 219.462,
      "duration": 1.845
    },
    {
      "text": "it's crucial principle is undermining",
      "start": 221.307,
      "duration": 3.691
    },
    {
      "text": "mechanisms of social solidarity",
      "start": 224.998,
      "duration": 2.583
    },
    {
      "text": "and mutual support",
      "start": 231.259,
      "duration": 1.255
    },
    {
      "text": "and popular engagement",
      "start": 232.514,
      "duration": 2.447
    },
    {
      "text": "in determining policy.",
      "start": 234.961,
      "duration": 2.054
    },
    {
      "text": "It's not called that.",
      "start": 237.015,
      "duration": 1.343
    },
    {
      "text": "What it's called is freedom.",
      "start": 238.358,
      "duration": 1.344
    },
    {
      "text": "- I'm not in favor of fairness.",
      "start": 239.702,
      "duration": 1.877
    },
    {
      "text": "I'm in favor of freedom.",
      "start": 241.579,
      "duration": 2.017
    },
    {
      "text": "And freedom is not fairness.",
      "start": 243.596,
      "duration": 1.896
    },
    {
      "text": "Fairness means somebody\nhas to decide what's fair.",
      "start": 245.492,
      "duration": 3.115
    },
    {
      "text": "- But freedom means subordination",
      "start": 248.607,
      "duration": 2.645
    },
    {
      "text": "to the decisions of concentrated,",
      "start": 251.252,
      "duration": 3.562
    },
    {
      "text": "unaccountable, private power.",
      "start": 254.814,
      "duration": 2.117
    },
    {
      "text": "That's what it means.",
      "start": 256.931,
      "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
      "text": "The institutions of governance",
      "start": 258.411,
      "duration": 2.281
    },
    {
      "text": "or other kinds of association",
      "start": 260.692,
      "duration": 2.362
    },
    {
      "text": "that could allow people to participate",
      "start": 263.054,
      "duration": 2.662
    },
    {
      "text": "in decision making.",
      "start": 265.716,
      "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
      "text": "Those are systematically weakened.",
      "start": 267.396,
      "duration": 2.976
    },
    {
      "text": "Margaret Thatcher said it rather nicely",
      "start": 270.372,
      "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
      "text": "in her aphorism about there is no society",
      "start": 273.132,
      "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
      "text": "only individuals.",
      "start": 276.132,
      "duration": 1.417
    },
    {
      "text": "She was actually, unconsciously no doubt,",
      "start": 279.032,
      "duration": 3.004
    },
    {
      "text": "paraphrasing Marx who in his condemnation",
      "start": 282.036,
      "duration": 3.417
    },
    {
      "text": "of the repression in France",
      "start": 286.733,
      "duration": 1.879
    },
    {
      "text": "said the repression is turning society",
      "start": 288.612,
      "duration": 3.167
    },
    {
      "text": "into a sack of potatoes.",
      "start": 292.713,
      "duration": 2.539
    },
    {
      "text": "That just individuals amorphous mass",
      "start": 295.252,
      "duration": 2.142
    },
    {
      "text": "can't act together.",
      "start": 297.394,
      "duration": 1.938
    },
    {
      "text": "That was a condemnation.",
      "start": 299.332,
      "duration": 1.424
    },
    {
      "text": "For Thatcher, it's an ideal.",
      "start": 300.756,
      "duration": 1.794
    },
    {
      "text": "And that's neoliberalism.",
      "start": 302.55,
      "duration": 2.083
    },
    {
      "text": "We destroy or at least undermine",
      "start": 305.652,
      "duration": 1.743
    },
    {
      "text": "the governing mechanisms in which people,",
      "start": 307.395,
      "duration": 3.417
    },
    {
      "text": "at least in principle,",
      "start": 312.485,
      "duration": 1.566
    },
    {
      "text": "can participate to the extent",
      "start": 314.051,
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "text": "the society's democratic.",
      "start": 316.051,
      "duration": 1.858
    },
    {
      "text": "So, we can then undermine unions",
      "start": 317.909,
      "duration": 3.483
    },
    {
      "text": "other forms of association,",
      "start": 321.392,
      "duration": 2.341
    },
    {
      "text": "leave a sack of potatoes,",
      "start": 323.733,
      "duration": 2.413
    },
    {
      "text": "and meanwhile transfer decisions",
      "start": 326.146,
      "duration": 3.274
    },
    {
      "text": "to unaccountable private power",
      "start": 329.42,
      "duration": 2.441
    },
    {
      "text": "all in the rhetoric of freedom.",
      "start": 331.861,
      "duration": 1.698
    },
    {
      "text": "Well, what does that do?",
      "start": 333.559,
      "duration": 2.544
    },
    {
      "text": "The one barrier to the threat",
      "start": 336.103,
      "duration": 2.837
    },
    {
      "text": "of destruction is an engaged public,",
      "start": 338.94,
      "duration": 2.077
    },
    {
      "text": "an informed, engaged\npublic acting together",
      "start": 341.017,
      "duration": 3.119
    },
    {
      "text": "to develop means to confront the threat",
      "start": 344.136,
      "duration": 3.324
    },
    {
      "text": "and respond to it.",
      "start": 347.46,
      "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
      "text": "And that's systematically weakened",
      "start": 350.249,
      "duration": 1.571
    },
    {
      "text": "for people to become more passive",
      "start": 351.82,
      "duration": 2.259
    },
    {
      "text": "and apathetic",
      "start": 354.079,
      "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
      "text": "and not disturb things too much.",
      "start": 355.399,
      "duration": 2.798
    },
    {
      "text": "And that's what the\nneoliberal programs do.",
      "start": 358.197,
      "duration": 2.445
    },
    {
      "text": "So, put it all together",
      "start": 360.642,
      "duration": 1.152
    },
    {
      "text": "and what do you have?",
      "start": 361.794,
      "duration": 1.466
    },
    {
      "text": "A perfect storm.",
      "start": 363.26,
      "duration": 1.333
    },
    {
      "text": "This is all very simple.",
      "start": 382.661,
      "duration": 1.639
    },
    {
      "text": "It's all in front of your eyes.",
      "start": 384.3,
      "duration": 2.281
    },
    {
      "text": "All you have to do is look.",
      "start": 386.581,
      "duration": 2.301
    },
    {
      "text": "Takes no profound intelligence,",
      "start": 388.882,
      "duration": 3.056
    },
    {
      "text": "takes no special insight.",
      "start": 391.938,
      "duration": 1.664
    },
    {
      "text": "Just look at what's in front of your eyes.",
      "start": 393.602,
      "duration": 3.317
    },
    {
      "text": "It's right there.",
      "start": 396.919,
      "duration": 1.417
    },
    {
      "text": "In fact, I think a lot of people see it.",
      "start": 399.66,
      "duration": 3.417
    }
  ]
}